Android Developer

Location

Lausanne

Company

Service Company

Responsibilities
• Take part in and oversee the development of secure, efficient Android applications, ensuring adherence to best practices and project specifications.
• Design and implement robust security protocols and features to safeguard apps against evolving cyber threats.
• Provide guidance and mentorship to junior developers, fostering a collaborative and productive team environment.
• Analyze and optimize app performance and security, ensuring superior user experience and reliability.
• Continuously research and implement new technologies and methodologies to maintain technological leadership in security-focused Android development.
• Conduct thorough code reviews and enforce coding standards across the development team.
• Tackle complex technical challenges and provide effective solutions.

Requirements
• Bachelor's or master's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
• Proficiency in Java/Kotlin or a similar language, with knowledge of Android Studio being a plus.

Please note that fluency in German at least at a C1 level, both orally and in writing, is required for this position.

jobs_results.title: Sr Android Developer
jobs_results.description:
As a Sr. Engineer - Android consultant, you will be working on pioneering technology in the hardware and software world. You will be merging the hardware features with software to provide a unified, smooth customer experience over Bluetooth stack, location-based services while prioritizing privacy and security of customer data.

Your will be interacting with product managers to help them discover Android features and capabilities, advise them on feasibility, provide estimations. You will be working with hardware engineers to connect apps with hardware and deliver functionality that is highly technical, and engineering focused.

Test driven development will your foundation for delivering quality code at source with unit tests, integration tests. You will lead the delivery of your code from end-to-end, automating continuous integration and delivery.

Skills Required
• Proficiency in Java and working knowledge with Kotlin
• Experience with Bluetooth stack, location services, GPS and maps
• Experience with Java/Kotlin, RxJava, gradle and jUnit, espresso testing.
• Understanding of Material design and mobile UX/UI patterns
• Deep experience-based understanding of how to build mobile applications at scale.
• Experience working in a team of Android developers participating in code reviews, pull requests, and pair programming.
• Validated experience mentoring and coaching other Android developers in a collaborative and team-based organization.
• Understanding of consuming RESTful web services, running authentication, authorization, and session
• Strong understanding of modern development principles such as trunk-based development, feature toggles, and branch by abstraction to support performant and collaborative engineering teams.
• Strong understanding of CI/CD tools such as Azure DevOps to continuously and autonomously deliver high-quality apps to guarantee stable and performant experiences.
• Experience working with multi-functional teams such as design, product, data teams to deliver great user experiences.
• Understanding of computer science fundamentals, data structures, and algorithms to ensure consistency to software engineering standard processes including object-oriented and functional programming

Skills Desired
• Exposure to Cloud or Firmware Development.
• Knowledgeable in asynchronous development, networking, or Bluetooth.
• Understanding of internet protocols such as TCP/IP, UDP and networking and security standards
• Familiarity with API development, database queries, backend systems
• Leadership experience

Qualifications
• 7-10 years of Android development experience
• Experience leading development teams
• Strong communication skills with ability to articulate effectively
• Bachelor's degree in STEM faculties
• Published Apps in the Play Store

Location:

Local to Bellevue, WA

jobs_results.title: Senior Android Developer
jobs_results.description:
Location: Sandhubel
Axon Vibe is a cutting-edge technology company building AI-powered mobility and contextual marketing solutions. We partner with leading and forward-thinking public transport operators like SBB, Deutsche Bahn, and MTA New York. Our innovative mobility and rewards platform enables smart and seamless mobility solutions, supports automatic ticketing and helps to increase public transport ridership through behaviour change and loyalty campaigns. Founded by veterans of Google Maps, Axon Vibe is committed to building sustainable solutions for the future of mobility and drive-to-store marketing.

Our mobile SDK is a key part of our platform and serves as the primary interface for partners when they integrate our technology into their products and services. We are looking for a Senior-level mobile engineer to join our team of existing mobile SDK developers.

Key Responsibilities Develop and maintain innovative features and modules in our mobile SDK, used by renowned public transport operators in the world.

Collaborate closely with other engineers and product owners to design new capabilities that drive the ongoing evolution and enhancement of our platform.

Engage directly with customers and partners, collaborating on projects to discuss, design and implement tailored solutions that address real-world challenges in mobility and marketing innovation.

Champion code quality through regular reviews, automated testing, and continuous integration, ensuring that our solutions are reliable, secure and scalable.

Play a key role in shaping and evolving our software design and development processes, contributing fresh ideas and improvements.

Oversee and maintain comprehensive SDK documentation and developer tools, including our internal testing applications.

Tackle complex issues with autonomy and collaborate with backend and Dev Ops teams.

Continuously fine-tune the performance, security, and resilience of our SDK to maintain our edge in the competitive mobile landscape.

Stay ahead of the curve by keeping up with the latest mobile OS updates, development tools, frameworks, and industry best practices. Qualifications 5+ years of senior-level experience in Android (Java/Kotlin) development

Deep expertise in Android frameworks and Google Play Services and a strong grasp of Android’s architectural principles

Knowledge about location, motion and other sensor frameworks, including Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE)

Experience with RESTful APIs, authentication (OAuth) and networking protocols

Skilled in asynchronous programming, including multi-threading, reactive programming and background processing

Comfortable with continuous integration and release pipelines and proficient in version control systems

Solid background in automated testing, including unit testing

Strong communicator and team player, comfortable working in a fast-paced, collaborative environment

Experienced in agile methodologies, particularly Scrum Fluency in English is essential;
German language skills are a plus Bonus Skills

Experience with cross-platform frameworks (React Native, Capacitor

JS, KMP, Flutter)
Full-stack experience (Java/Spring) and knowledge of the AWS ecosystem

Experience with on-device machine learning models

Experience with publishing apps to the Google Play Store and Apple App Store Work in an international team, and with international customers

Please send your cover letter and resume detailing your experience and relevant projects to Please include links to any apps you have developed or contributed to.

We will not consider applications submitted by a recruitment agency. Candidates must get in touch with us directly.

jobs_results.title: Senior Android Engineer FinTech
jobs_results.description:
As a Senior Android Engineer, you will be working directly with our design team and product managers with a focus on our Android application. You will join a growing team of engineers to create a revolutionary mobile experience and work on our most strategic channel, impacting hundreds of thousands of customers every month.

Team Mission:

The FinTech team's mission is to provide a seamless checkout experience to our customers. Being the main Android engineer in the team, you will take ownership of the existing checkout experience and work together with the team to take it to the next level. Your tasks will range from defining and implementing architectural evolution, over monitoring, and stability improvements together with backend engineers, to UX evolution with A/B testing in collaboration with our product manager and our UX team.

Responsibilities:
• Contribute to the development of GetYourGuide’s native Android app
• Implement new features in the app and improve the user experience
• Contribute significantly to the team’s app roadmap
• Shape and improve the app’s architecture
• Maintain a high standard of quality for our code, features, and products
• Translate high-level ideas and requirements into practical solutions
• Contribute to learning and advancement of our engineering practice

Requirements:
• Product and data-centric prioritization and decision making
• Ability to turn ideas into solid, maintainable code
• Drive to improve; proactively identify problems and bring solutions
• High proficiency with Java and Kotlin
• Know your way around the Android SDK and Android Jetpack
• Open to learning new technologies and methodologies
• Positive, pro-active team player who is passionate about their craft
• Excellent English communication skills (orally and written)

Nice to Have:
• Have one or more successful Android apps published in the Google Play store
• Good knowledge of the following tools: Git, Github, IntelliJ/Android Studio, Gradle, Jira
• Experience with Koin, Room, RX, Coroutines, and JUnit/Espresso
• Experience with iOS development and Swift
• Experience with backend development (Java or PHP)

We Offer:
• Work on a product that helps create memorable travel experiences
• Be part of an international team from over 70 nationalities
• Quarterly Hackathons and weekly tech talks
• GetYourGuide gift cards to experience our products for yourself
• Virtual stock options that make you an integral part of the company’s growth and success

Curious?

Do you have the skills for the job, enthusiasm about our vision, and fit our culture? We are already looking forward to hearing from you! If you have any further questions please do not hesitate to contact us via jobs@getyourguide.com.

In the meantime, you can check our blog to get some insights on fixing bugs and how one of our Android developers sets up his projects. Check out other topics on our blog to see what happens behind the scenes at GetYourGuide and check out Tech Radar for an insight into the stack we use to turn our customers’ dreams' into reality!
